<L>__{interior beacon hotel night}
<A>__{doc and carol are getting ready for bed. it is the night before the robbery. carol stands looking in the mirror.}
<C>__{carol}
<D>__{you know how i feel?}
<C>__{doc}
<D>__{my mind's not on guessing games.}
<A>__{carol turns away from the mirror.}
<C>__{carol}
<D>__{promise you won't laugh.}
<C>__{doc}
<P>__{(shakes his head; smiles)}
<D>__{if it's funny i'm going to laugh.}
<C>__{carol}
<D>__{i feel like the night before the first day of school.}
<C>__{doc}
<D>__{that bad?}
<A>__{carol laughs.}
<C>__{doc }
<D>__{you promised not to laugh.}
<A>__{they both laugh. long beat. carol gets into bed. doc is already in bed.}
<C>__{carol}
<D>__{it will be such a relief not to have to think about it any more.}
<C>__{doc}
<D>__{waiting's hard. you never learn how.}
<C>__{carol}
<D>__{you know i've actually gotten tired waiting sometimes... worn out waiting.}
<C>__{doc}
<D>__{at least you were outside.}
<C>__{carol}
<D>__{it doesn!t make much difference where you are, if you're waiting, doc.}
